v:4 c:$ m:portfolio role:dev x:vite-glob-imports
gate: LOCKED

task: Build the Room registry — auto-discovers every `src/rooms/*/room.config.ts` at build time, validates each manifest, sorts, and exposes typed accessors. Single source of truth for Wall, router (T12), and Supabase analytics.

requires: [vite, typescript]
out:
  - app/src/rooms/_sdk/registry.ts
  - app/src/rooms/_sdk/loader.ts
  - app/src/rooms/_sdk/__tests__/registry.spec.ts
  - app/src/rooms/index.ts (public barrel)

discovery:
  - manifests: import.meta.glob('/src/rooms/*/room.config.ts', { eager: true })
  - components: import.meta.glob('/src/rooms/*/Room.vue')   (lazy, NOT eager)
  - keyed by directory name (must equal manifest.slug — registry asserts this).

api:
  - getAllRooms(): RoomManifest[]                         (filtered by env: drops draft in prod)
  - getPublicRooms(): RoomManifest[]                      (visibility==='public', for Wall)
  - getRoomBySlug(slug): RoomManifest | null
  - loadRoomComponent(slug): () => Promise<Component>     (returns dynamic import)
  - isPitchRoom(slug): boolean

filters:
  - import.meta.env.PROD: drop status==='draft' AND visibility==='draft'
  - dev: include everything

validation (run once at module init):
  - all manifests must pass RoomManifestSchema (T09)
  - slug-to-dir match enforced (manifest.slug must equal containing folder name)
  - no duplicate slugs across folders
  - on failure: throw at boot — better to crash dev than ship a broken Wall

constraints:
  - Registry module is import-once (cached at module level).
  - No async work in getters — only at boot.
  - Public barrel `rooms/index.ts` re-exports api + types from `_sdk/`.

done:
  - Adding a new dir `src/rooms/foo/` with valid manifest auto-appears in `getAllRooms()`.
  - Invalid manifest fails build with clear path + zod error.
  - Vitest covers: discovery, slug-mismatch, duplicate-slug, env filtering.
  - Tree-shaking verified: prod bundle excludes draft rooms (check dist).
